  "title": "Cadaver Synod",
  "description": "In this new dark comedy by the creators of 638 Ways to Kill Castro, a medieval emperor and his allies take on an absurd task; dig up the long-dead Pope who betrayed them, and put his corpse on trial. But between riots in the Vatican and growing signs that the Pope may not be so dead after all, can they survive the Cadaver Synod?",
  "credits": "<strong>Playwright</strong>: Sebastian Ley<br/><strong>Director</strong>: Kathleen Weiss<br/><strong>Cast</strong>: Samuel Bronson, David Ley, Michael Watt<br/><strong>Designers</strong>: Sarah Fett<br/><strong>Stage Manager</strong>: Lauren Belter<br/>",
  "website": "https://vaulttheatre.net | https://instagram.com/vaulttheatreyeg",
  "plain_language": "Cadaver Synod happens in the Dark Ages. It follows the story of an ill-fated plan to put the dead body of a Pope on trial. From the creators of 638 Ways to Kill Castro, this new dark comedy is based on true history.",
